Wrapping up
The whole thing — scaffold to working cross-framework widget — was maybe an hour, and most of that was me reading release notes. Module federation still earns its complexity when many large apps share heavy dependencies under one org’s discipline. But for “my team ships a widget, your team embeds it” — which is what most micro frontend problems actually are — web components are the boring, durable answer. And boring seams are the best seams.
If you build something with this, I’d love to hear how it goes — especially if you hit a gotcha I missed. Find me at pipdev.net.
